00:21:45.300 --> 00:21:51.300
tools, and the centralized management that makes it easier for IT to administer the various

00:21:51.300 --> 00:21:59.300
IDEs supported by Posit Workbench from a single platform, reducing overhead.

00:21:59.300 --> 00:22:04.300
If it's not already clear from our demo today, I hope you can tell that in designing Positron

00:22:04.300 --> 00:22:09.300
and deciding which features and capabilities will require a Pro license, Posit takes a

00:22:09.300 --> 00:22:11.300
different approach.

00:22:11.300 --> 00:22:14.300
Our commitment to providing collaborative and innovative open source software for data

00:22:14.300 --> 00:22:19.300
science, our commitment to giving data teams choice and autonomy to use software in the

00:22:19.300 --> 00:22:24.300
way that they believe makes the most sense, and our commitment to balance our profitability

00:22:24.300 --> 00:22:29.300
with the benefits we provide to our customers and community, whether they pay us any revenue

00:22:29.300 --> 00:22:34.300
or not, is a core part of our identity as a company, and is codified in our corporate

00:22:34.300 --> 00:22:37.300
charter as a public benefit corporation.

00:22:37.300 --> 00:22:42.300
To learn more about our mission as a company, you can visit posit.co.pbc.

00:22:42.300 --> 00:22:44.300
Thank you.

